"```sql\nSELECT t.balance, c.gender\nFROM trans t\nJOIN disp d ON t.account_id = d.account_id\nJOIN client c ON d.client_id = c.client_id\nWHERE t.trans_id = 851 AND c.client_id = 4;\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the balance of the account following transaction 851 and the gender of the client who owns the account. It joins the `trans`, `disp`, and `client` tables using the foreign key relationships to find the relevant information for client number 4."